body: Here are a few resources to help you get started. Welcome to MongoDB Ready to get your first MongoDB cluster up and running? Start with these four steps: * Create cluster <[www.mongodb.com](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/atlas/tutorial/deploy-free-tier-cluster/>) * Add IP address to access list <[www.mongodb.com](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/atlas/security/add-ip-address-to-list/>) * Create a user <[www.mongodb.com](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/atlas/tutorial/create-mongodb-user-for-cluster/>) * Connect to cluster <[www.mongodb.com](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/atlas/tutorial/connect-to-your-cluster/>) If you re more of a visual learner, we ve put together a six-minute video <[learn.mongodb.com](https://learn.mongodb.com/courses/getting-started-with-mongodb-atlas>) that guides you through cluster setup. <[learn.mongodb.com](https://learn.mongodb.com/courses/getting-started-with-mongodb-atlas>) Next, you can start building. subject: Making the most of Cursor
body: Hi Juber, Your free plan for Cursor is now active. Thank you for trying out the editor. Here are a few things you can try in Cursor: - Type and press Tab to accept an autocomplete or a suggested diff from Cursor Tab - Open Agent in Chat to make multi-file edits and hand off simpler tasks - Select 20 lines of code and press Cmd+K to make an inline edit You can find more tips in the docs . Feel free to shoot any questions or thoughts to our forum . Best, The Cursor Devs If you don't want to hear from me again, please let me know .
